    "(3) Cutlery Drawer Interaction: The cutlery drawer is also open, indicating that the subject may be preparing to use utensils, which is typically associated with meal preparation or eating.",
    "(4) Sequence of Actions: • The subject first has the fridge open and the cutlery drawer open, suggesting they are gathering items.",
    "• They close the fridge after 1 second, which could indicate they retrieved something.",
    "• They then open the fridge again, which suggests they might be looking for more items or confirming what they have.",
    "• After 4 seconds, they close the fridge again, indicating they have finished gathering items."
